cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CVPR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting and segmenting objects in real-time using RGB-D data. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the system for SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) which is a common problem in robotics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses a novel method combining 2D object detection and 3D geometric segmentation for real-time instance segmentation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques for object detection and segmentation. 
- cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper presents a new method for real-time instance segmentation which is a common problem in CVPR.
